icleshow%2F102181996.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20change%20the%20refresh%20rate%20on%20your%20monitor%20for%20smoother-looking%20videos%20and%20gameplay%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224009%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20wearing%20over%20ear%20headphones%20shown%20from%20behind%20in%20silhouette%20gaming%20on%20a%20computer.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6063b0cc6183e100198196da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222004%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20high%20refresh%20rate%20on%20a%20monitor%20is%20especially%20important%20for%20gaming%2C%20which%20requires%20an%20on-screen%20image%20to%20rapidly%20refresh.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Kraus%2FEyeEm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20monitor's%20refresh%20rate%20measures%20how%20frequently%20the%20on-screen%20image%20is%20updated.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EYou%20can%20change%20the%20refresh%20rate%20on%20your%20monitor%20through%20your%20display%20settings%2C%20though%20it%20may%20be%20limited%20by%20the%20monitor%2C%20graphics%20card%2C%20and%20screen%20resolution.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20typical%20refresh%20rate%20is%2060Hz%3B%20slower%20refresh%20rates%20can%20look%20jittery%2C%20while%20higher%20refresh%20rates%20are%20desirable%20for%20gaming.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20monitor's%20refresh%20rate%20is%20a%20measure%20of%20how%20frequently%20the%20on-screen%20image%20is%20updated.%20Refresh%20rate%20is%20measured%20in%20hertz%20(Hz)%2C%20which%20indicates%20the%20number%20of%20times%20per%20second%20something%20occurs.%20So%20a%2060Hz%20display%20is%20one%20that%20has%20a%20refresh%20rate%20of%2060%20times%20per%20second.%20Higher%20fresh%20rates%20can%20produce%20smoother%20images%2C%20which%20can%20be%20especially%20beneficial%20for%20gamers.%20That's%20why%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-gaming-monitor%5C%22%3Ebest%20gaming%20monitors%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-gaming-laptop%5C%22%3Ebest%20gaming%20laptops%3C%2Fa%3E%20use%20high%20refresh%20rate%20screens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUnderstanding%20monitor%20refresh%20rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20don't%20need%20to%20worry%20much%20about%20refresh%20rate%2C%20especially%20when%20using%20a%20computer%20for%20ordinary%20productivity%20applications.%20That's%20because%20computer%20displays%20typically%20have%20a%20refresh%20rate%20of%2060Hz%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20the%20default%20for%20many%20monitors%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20value%20is%20perfectly%20adequate%20almost%20all%20the%20time.%20It's%20fast%20enough%20that%20there's%20no%20obvious%20blurring%20or%20%26quot%3Bimage%20tearing%26quot%3B%20when%20there's%20on-screen%20motion.%20Below%20this%20value%20%E2%80%94%2030%20Hz%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20you%20might%20see%20some%20stuttering%20or%20jitteriness%20when%20things%20are%20moving%20on%20the%20screen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigher%20refresh%20rates%20are%20of%20interest%20to%20gamers%2C%20though.%20Because%20many%20video%20games%20rely%20on%20fast-moving%20visuals%2C%20many%20computer%20displays%20are%20optimized%20for%20gaming%20with%20very%20high%20refresh%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20144Hz%2C%20240Hz%2C%20and%20even%20360Hz.%C2%A0%20Higher%20frame%20rates%20can%20also%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20react%20to%20things%20happening%20on%20screen.%20For%20gaming%2C%20the%20higher%20the%20refresh%20rate%20the%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeep%20in%20mind%2C%20however%2C%20that%20even%20if%20you%20have%20a%20high%20refresh%20rate%20monitor%2C%20in%20order%20to%20actually%20take%20advantage%20of%20its%20smoother%20motion%20during%20gameplay%20you'll%20need%20gaming%20hardware%20that's%20powerful%20enough%20to%20run%20games%20at%20a%20high%20frame%20rate.%20Check%20out%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-gaming-pc%5C%22%3Ebest%20gaming%20PCs%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20some%20of%20our%20top%20recommendations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20relationship%20between%20screen%20resolution%20and%20refresh%20rate.%20Because%20computers%20and%20video%20game%20consoles%20only%20have%20so%20much%20bandwidth%20for%20the%20display%2C%20you%20might%20find%20that%20at%20higher%20resolutions%2C%20your%20display%20can't%20run%20at%20its%20maximum%20refresh%20rate.%20If%20you%20are%20adjusting%20these%20settings%2C%20you%20might%20need%20to%20make%20a%20choice%20between%2C%20for%20example%2C%20an%20HD%20(1920x1080)%20display%20at%20144Hz%20or%20a%204K%20(3840x2160)%20resolution%20at%2060Hz.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20your%20monitor%20or%20laptop%20display%2C%20you%20might%20be%20able%20to%20adjust%20the%20refresh%20rate.%20Some%20displays%20aren't%20running%20at%20their%20highest%20refresh%20rate%20by%20default%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20it's%20adjustable%20in%20the%20system%20settings.%20If%20you%20try%20to%20increase%20the%20refresh%20rate%20but%20it%20won't%20go%20as%20high%20as%20you%20think%20the%20monitor%20is%20designed%20to%20go%2C%20you%20might%20need%20to%20lower%20the%20resolution%20to%20make%20a%20higher%20value%20become%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20change%20the%20refresh%20rate%20on%20your%20PC%20monitor%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20open%20the%20refresh%20rate%20settings%20on%20any%20Windows%20PC%2C%20though%20whether%20you%20can%20change%20it%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20values%20you%20can%20set%20%E2%80%94%20depend%20on%20your%20graphics%20card%2C%20monitor%20or%20laptop%20display%2C%20and%20the%20resolution%20you%20are%20running.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EClick%20the%20Start%20button%20and%20click%20%26quot%3BSettings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClick%20%26quot%3BSystem%26quot%3B%20and%20then%2C%20in%20the%20navig