vard%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20in%20the%20spotlight%20after%20the%20Education%20Department%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F25%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fharvard-admissions-civil-rights-inquiry.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopened%20an%20inquiry%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%20school's%20admissions%20process%20following%20allegations%20from%20three%20groups%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Chica%20Project%2C%20the%20African%20Community%20Economic%20Development%20of%20New%20England%2C%20and%20the%20Greater%20Boston%20Latino%20Network%20%E2%80%94%20that%20claimed%20Harvard%20was%20favoring%20white%20and%20wealthy%20applications%20who%20were%20less%20qualified%20over%20applicants%20of%20color.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Harvard%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20is%20examining%20data%20on%20the%20way%20it%20admits%20students%2C%20and%20that%20%26quot%3BHarvard%20remains%20dedicated%20to%20opening%20doors%20to%20opportunity%20and%20to%20redoubling%20our%20efforts%20to%20encourage%20students%20from%20many%20different%20backgrounds%20to%20apply%20for%20admission.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20schools%20like%20Johns%20Hopkins%20and%20Amherst%20have%20ditched%20the%20preference%20for%20legacy%20students%20altogether%2C%20Harvard%20has%20so%20far%20declined%20to%20do%20so.%20A%202018%20Harvard%20committee%20to%20study%20the%20role%20of%20diversity%20in%20education%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.iq.harvard.edu%2Ffiles%2Fdiverse-education%2Ffiles%2Freport_of_the_committee_to_study_race-neutral_alternatives_final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20getting%20rid%20of%20a%20legacy%20preference%20could%20diminish%20donations%20from%20alumni.%20Here's%20how%20important%20those%20donations%20are%20to%20one%20of%20the%20richest%20schools%20in%20the%20country%20and%20how%20it%20spends%20its%20billions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHarvard%20has%20the%20biggest%20endowment%20in%20the%20country%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard%20has%20the%20biggest%20endowment%20in%20the%20US%2C%20totaling%20just%20over%20%2450%20billion%20as%20of%20fiscal%20year%202022.%20The%20endowment%20is%20made%20up%20of%20more%20than%2014%2C000%20funds%2C%20and%20according%20to%20the%20schools'%20fiscal%20year%202022%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.harvard.edu%2Ffiles%2Ffad%2Ffiles%2Ffy22_harvard_financial_report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Bendowment%20fund%20balances%20are%20classified%20and%20reported%20in%20accordance%20with%20donor%20specifications%20and%20state%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Harvard%20fiscal%20year%202022%20operating%20revenue%20sources%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c2b465cf07780019659069%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22487%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHarvard%20fiscal%20year%202022%20operating%20revenue%20sources.%3Cp%3EHarvard%20University%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20university%20does%20not%20disclose%20where%20individual%20donations%20come%20from%2C%20there%20is%20a%20breakdown%20of%20broad%20categories%20that%20contribute%20to%20the%20endowment%20%E2%80%94%20and%20where%20the%20money%20goes.%20According%20to%20the%20school's%202022%20financial%20report%2C%20philanthropy%2C%20which%20includes%20gifts%20from%20donors%20and%20alumni%2C%20accounted%20for%2045%25%20of%20total%20revenue.%20Research%20accounted%20for%2017%25%2C%20education%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20like%20tuition%2C%20room%2C%20and%20board%20%E2%80%94%20accounted%20for%2021%25%2C%20and%20other%20sources%20like%20publications%20accounted%20for%2017%25%20of%20the%20school's%20total%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20fiscal%20year%202022%2C%20Harvard%20received%20current%20use%20gifts%20from%20alumni%2C%20foundations%2C%20and%2