e%20the%20third%20largest%20economy%2C%20with%20China%20and%20US%20in%20first%20and%20second%20positions%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20another%20projection%2C%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPankajPachauri%2Fstatus%2F1684499399068758017%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3EStatista%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Pachauri%20has%20said%20that%20the%20Indian%20economy%20was%20to%20have%20become%20third%20largest%20in%202024%20but%20that%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20promise%20of%20this%20occurring%20in%20the%20course%20of%20his%20possible%20third%20term%20pushes%20the%20deadline%20to%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20also%20pointed%20out%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20founding%20editor%20M.K.%20Venu%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imf.org%2Fexternal%2Fdatamapper%2FPPPSH%40WEO%2FOEMDC%2FADVEC%2FWEOWORLD%5C%22%3Ealready%20the%20third%20largest%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20world%20in%20purchasing%20power%20parity%20or%20PPP%20terms.%20This%20has%20been%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20has%20seen%20%E2%80%9Cbelow%20potential%20growth%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years%2C%20Venu%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Pachauri%20and%20Venu%20noted%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20that%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20latest%20words%20reflected%20the%20trend%20of%20him%20forever%20shifting%20economic%20goal%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98%245-trillion%20economy%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20case%20in%20point%20is%20that%20in%202019%2C%20Modi%20himself%20had%20envisioned%20that%20India%20would%20become%20a%20%E2%80%9C%245%20trillion%20economy%20by%202024-2025.%E2%80%9D%20His%20promise%20was%20featured%20multiple%20times%20as%20he%20sought%20and%20won%20a%20second%20time%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20important%20to%20know%20about%20this%20because%20there%20are%20some%20people%20who%20doubt%20the%20capabilities%20of%20Indians.%20They%20are%20saying%20it%20is%20very%20difficult%20for%20India%20to%20achieve%20this%20goal.%20However%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20courage%2C%20of%20new%20possibilities%2C%20of%20the%20sacrificial%20fire%20of%20development%2C%20of%20serving%20Maa%20Bharati%2C%20and%20dreaming%20of%20New%20India.%20These%20dreams%20are%20largely%20linked%20to%20the%20goal%20of%20%245%20trillion%20economy%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fpm-modi-varanasi-5-trillion-economy-budget-1563362-2019-07-06%5C%22%3EModi%20had%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20mid-June%2C%202023%2C%20Union%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%E2%80%99s%20office%20tweeted%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20had%20touched%20the%20%243.75%20trillion%20mark%20in%202023.%20This%20would%20mean%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20%245-trillion%20figure%20is%20still%20a%20long%20way%20off%20and%20quite%20difficult%20considering%20the%202024-25%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESitharaman%20is%20not%20the%20only%20government%20figure%20who%20has%20spoken%20of%20trillion%20figures%20that%20fall%20short%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20initial%20%E2%80%98%245-trillion%20economy%E2%80%99%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Sitharaman%E2%80%99s%20tweet%20mentioned%20%243.75%20trillion%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20chief%20economic%20advisor%20V.%20Anantha%20Nageswaran%20had%20earlier%20in%20the%20year%20said%20that%20the%20Indian%20economy%20will%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9C%243%20trillion%20one%20at%20current%20prices%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%202022-23%20fiscal%20year%E2%80%9D.%20Nageswaran%20also%20said%20that%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20touch%20the%20%247-trillion%20mark%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20next%20seven%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ffive-trillion-dollar-economy-india%5C%22%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%20earlier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Bibek%20Debroy%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20Economic%20Advisory%20C