nge-elon-musk%5C%22%3Eshort-lived%20thickening%20of%20the%20lines%3C%2Fa%3E%20going%20live%20on%20July%2026%2C%20before%20Musk%20announced%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20like%20it%20and%20would%20revert.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELinda%20Yaccarino%2C%20Twitter%E2%80%99s%20CEO%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2023%2F05%2F12%2Ftwitter-ceo-linda-yaccarino-elon-musk-glass-cliff-female-leaders%2F%5C%22%3Epotential%20scapegoat%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20the%20rebrand%20goes%20wrong%2C%20also%20confirmed%20the%20launch%20on%20Sunday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Flindayacc%2Fstatus%2F1683353772917940225%5C%22%3Etweeting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CX%20is%20here!%20Let%E2%80%99s%20do%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20a%20radical%20rebrand%20ever%20succeeded%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Facebook%20rebranded%20its%20holding%20company%20to%20Meta.%20But%20it%20kept%20%E2%80%9CFacebook%E2%80%9D%2C%20gave%20us%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fwhat-is-the-metaverse%2F%5C%22%3Emetaverse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20deprive%20the%20world%20of%20a%20cute%20feathery%20icon%20and%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctweeting%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBranding%20experts%20around%20the%20globe%20have%20been%20quick%20to%20condemn%20the%20Twitter%20shakeup%20as%20too%20sudden%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-x-rebrand-tech-marketing-brand-value-2023-7%5C%22%3Edestructive%20of%20brand%20capital%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%E2%80%99s%20perhaps%20because%20even%20slight%20name%20changes%20are%20known%20to%20be%20risky.%20Kentucky%20Fried%20Chicken%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.snopes.com%2Ffact-check%2Fkfc-and-fried%2F%5C%22%3Eofficially%20rebranded%20to%20KFC%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Pepsi%20was%20once%20Pepsi-Cola.%20These%20successful%20adjustments%20took%20time%20and%20careful%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDramatic%20renaming%20of%20a%20household%20name%20has%20basically%20never%20worked.%20And%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20a%20black%20%E2%80%9CX%E2%80%9D%20replacing%20%E2%80%9CTwitter%E2%80%9D%20is%20dramatic.%20It%20smashes%20the%20metaphor%20of%20birds%20updating%20one%20another%20in%20an%20idyllic%20blue-sky%20ecosystem.%20Sentimental%20fans%20holding%20out%20for%20a%20return%20to%20the%20good%20old%20days%20have%20now%20got%20the%20memo%3A%20Twitter%20isn%E2%80%99t%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20perhaps%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20point.%20To%20me%2C%20X%20%E2%80%93%20a%20symbol%20that%20can%20be%20a%20cattle%20marker%20or%20an%20illiterate%20signature%20%E2%80%93%20seems%20like%20a%20probe%20to%20perturb%20and%20test%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%20isn%E2%80%99t%20renaming%20fast%20food%20or%20soft%20drinks.%20Twitter%20is%20in%20the%20hyper-dynamic%20business%20of%20information.%20Musk%20is%20agile%20and%20well%20armed.%20So%20maybe%20new%20branding%20rules%20are%20being%20forged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%E2%80%99s%20progressive%20alienation%20of%20Twitter%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20users%20could%20be%20an%20attempt%20to%20refresh%20the%20platform%E2%80%99s%20demographic%20%E2%80%93%20to%20draw%20in%20those%20true%20to%20his%20other%20brands%2C%20while%20shaking%20off%20unprofitable%20sceptics.%20This%20would%20certainly%20fit%20with%20the%20push%20X%20gives%20towards%20Musk%E2%80%99s%20other%20X%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20commentators%20have%20latched%20onto%20the%20idea%20the%20change%20is%20sudden%2C%20irreversible%2C%20and%20complete%20in%20one%20day.%20But%20Musk%E2%80%99s%20past%20business%20endeavours%20suggest%20he%20is%20a%20strategist.%20The%20change%20will%20take%20time%20to%20play%20out%20and%20can%20likely%20be%20revised%2C%20reversed%20and%20adjusted%20as%20feedback%20is%20generated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoesn%E2%80%99t%20someone%20else%20own%20the%20%E2%80%9CX%E2%80%9D%20trademark%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrademarking%20of%20%E2%80%9CX%E2%80%9D%20is%20probably%20not%20pivotal%20to%20the%20Twitter%20rebrand.%20But%20achieving%20limited%20ownership%20of%20the%20letter%20is%20not%20as%20preposterous%20as%20it%20sounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrademarks%20are%20granted%20or%20refused%20based%20on%20their%20ability%20to%20identify%20the%20source%20of%20the%20associated%20goods%20or%20services.%20This%20means%20X%20can%20function%20as%20a%20trademark%20if%20it%20clearly%20identifies%20Twitter%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20public%20(provided%20another%20Twitter-like%20service%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20currently%20hold%20the%20trademark).%20Famous%20brands%20have%20advantages%3A%20Musk%20has%20already%20garnered%20enough%20media%20attention%20to%20ensure%20X%20is%20now%20a%20globally%20recognised%20term%20for%20his%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20X%20a%20generic%20term%20and%20thus%20not%20trademarkable%3F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F01622439211055482%5C%22%3EMy%20own%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20argues%20trademarks%20used%20by%20tech%20firms%20involved%20in%20consumer%20search%20and%20decision%20making%20(like%20Twitter)%20are%20inherently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FGeneric_trademark%5C%22%3Egeneric%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20under%20the%2077-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.law.cornell.edu%2Fwex%2Flanham_act%5C%22%3ELanham%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20still%20governs%20trademarks%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20X%20would%20have%20to%20be%20a%20common%20generic%20name%20for%20%3Cem%3Eall%3C%2Fem%3E%20services%20like%20Twitter%20to%20be%20refused.%20It%20isn%E2%80%99t.%20It%E2%80%99s%20mostly%20just%20a%20generic%20term%20for%20the%2024th%20letter%20of%20the%20alphabet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeculation%20about%20the%20legality%20of%20X%20as%20a%20trademark%20is%20one%20thing.%20My%20time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldtrademarkreview.com%2Fsearch%3Fsearch%3Dshackell%26sort%3D2%26page%3D1%5C%22%3Ewriting%20about%20