pan%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoradabad%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Since%20his%20early%20teens%2C%2045-year-old%20Ashaqeel%20(who%20goes%20only%20by%20his%20first%20name)%20has%20been%20working%20as%20an%20artisan%20smelting%20and%20casting%20brass%20in%20a%20cubby-hole%20furnace%20area%2C%20in%20the%20Peerzada%20locality%20of%20western%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Moradabad.%20But%20despite%20over%20three%20decades%20of%20work%2C%20he%20has%20never%20felt%20as%20anxious%20about%20his%20prospects%20as%20he%20does%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ELocal%20authorities%20have%20increasingly%20raised%20concerns%20about%20our%20brass%20production%20units%2C%20labelling%20them%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2FMoradabad-Metal-Workers-Oppose-UP-Pollution-Board-Close-Metal-Factories%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20be%20polluters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20we%E2%80%99ve%20been%20asked%20to%20relocate%20or%20shift%20to%20different%20methods%20of%20production.%20Where%20do%20we%20go%20when%20we%E2%80%99ve%20been%20working%20here%20for%20the%20past%20three%20decades%20and%20beyond%3F%E2%80%9D%20a%20weary%20Ashaqeel%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoradabad%20was%20once%20known%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epeetal%20nagri%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(brass%20city)%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20now%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20locals%20involved%20in%20the%20industry%20are%20expressing%20unease%20at%20what%20they%20see%20as%20an%20increasingly%20bleak%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20famous%20brass%20industry%20being%20part%20of%20the%20Union%20and%20UP%20government%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20%E2%80%98One%20District%20One%20Product%E2%80%99%20scheme%2C%20demand%20for%20the%20metal%20has%20declined.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20brass%20industry%20is%20now%20worth%20Rs%208%2C000-9%2C000%20crore%20at%20best.%20Until%202008-09%2C%20the%20turnover%20was%20at%20least%20Rs%2020%2C000%20crores%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20member%20of%20Moradabad%E2%80%99s%20Brass%20Manufacturers%20Association%2C%20Azam%20Ansari%2C%20informed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20former%20board%20member%20in%20the%20All%20India%20Handicrafts%20Board%20stressed%20that%20the%20sharp%20decline%20in%20the%20metal%E2%80%99s%20international%20demand%20had%20also%20affected%20them.%20%E2%80%9COver%2050%25%20of%20brass%20manufacturing%20units%20and%2025-30%25%20of%20our%20export%20units%20have%20shut%20down%20in%20the%20last%20decade%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20pointed%20out.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlready%20under%20distress%20since%20the%20twin%20blows%20of%20demonetisation%20and%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20(GST)%2C%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20raw%20materials%20and%20coal%20forced%20thousands%20to%20migrate.%20Brass%20is%20now%20said%20to%20make%20up%20just%2020-25%25%20of%20the%20metal%20industry%20in%20Moradabad.%20%E2%80%9CAluminium%20has%20taken%20over%20and%20is%20now%20at%20least%2070%25%20of%20the%20industry%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ansari%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoradabad%E2%80%99s%20industry%20has%20a%20three-stage%20production%20process%2C%20starting%20with%20artisans%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekarigars%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20who%20form%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20trade%20and%20undertake%20the%20work%20of%20casting%2C%20engraving%20and%20polishing%20the%20metal.%20The%20two%20other%20prominent%20players%20are%20the%20manufacturers%20and%20exporters.%20The%20divide%20between%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethree%20types%20of%20workers%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%20widened%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20son%20of%20an%20exporter%20has%20access%20to%20more%20profits%2C%20more%20money.%20If%20the%20exporter%20is%20making%20Rs%206%2C000%20on%20a%20big%20order%2C%20the%20manufacturer%20makes%20Rs%204%2C000-5%2C000%20while%20the%20artisan%20makes%20Rs%20500-600%20at%20best%20and%20is%20still%20a%20piece-rate%20labourer%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%2052-year-old%20Mujeeb-ur-Rahman%2C%20who%20has%20been%20casting%20metal%20in%20kilns%20for%20over%20four%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20wages%20and%20profits%20have%20stagnated%2C%20the%20latent%20impact%20of%20communalism%20has%20also%20made%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20once-thriving%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFor%20Muslim-owned%20businesses%20and%20workers%2C%20flashbacks%20to%20post-riot%20economic%20distress%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClose%20to%2047%25%20of%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20population%20is%20Muslim%20and%20many%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20the%20brass%20industry.%20Amongst%20the%20various%20stages%20of%20production%2C%20Muslims%20have%20traditionally%20dominated%20in%20artisan%20and%20manufacturing%20roles.%20At%20present%2C%20there%20are%20approximately%204%2C000%20exporters%20of%20brass%20in%20Moradabad%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20whom%20are%20Hindus%2C%20according%20to%20both%20Azam%20Ansari%20and%20Z.S.%20Mansoori%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Peetal%20Basti%20Dastkar%20Association.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20manufacturers%20and%20at%20least%2080%25%20of%20the%20artisans%20are%20Muslim.%20Hindus%20are%20more%20involved%20in%20the%20labour%20in%20terms%20of%20packaging%20and%20polishing%2C%E2%80%9D%20Azam%20Ansari%20said.%20At%20present%2C%20there%20are%20around%2030-40%2C000%20manufacturers%20and%20close%20to%202.5%20lakh%20labourers%20and%20artisans%20in%20the%20city%20%E2%80%93%20which%20Ansari%20claims%20is%20a%20decline%20from%20the%20over%20five%20lakh%20persons%20employed%20in%20the%20industry%20in%20its%20heydays.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20590px)%2085vw%2C%20590px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26170738%2Funnamed-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22590%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26170738%2Funnamed-1.jpg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26170738%2Funnamed-1-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26170738%2Funnamed-1-768x1024.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665263%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22787%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERaees%20Ahmed%20and%20his%20associates%20in%20Moradabad%E2%80%99s%20Peerzada%20locality%20working%20on%20engraving%20brass%20urns%20to%20be%20shipped%20abroad.%20Photo%3A%20Sabah%20Gurmat%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20city%20has%20also%20been%20the%20site%20of%20UP%E2%80%99s%20earliest%20large-scale%20communal%20riots%20in%201980%20%E2%80%93%20the%20biggest%20since%20Partition.%20A%20wave%20of%20violence%20began%20owing%20to%20tensions%20between%20local%20Muslims%20and%20Hindu%20Dalit%20groups%20near%20the%20Idgah%20area.%20This%20culminated%20on%20the%20day%20of%20Eid%20in%20August%2C%201980%2C%20after%20rumours%20spread%20that%20Hindus%20in%20the%20area%20had%20released%20a%20pig%20in%20the%20mosque.%20Muslims%20present%20there%20requested%20the%20police%20to%20remove%20the%20animal%20but%20to%20no%20avail.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20things%20became%20heated%2C%20a%20few%20stones%20were%20pelted%20on%20the%20police%2C%20following%20which%20the%20stationed%20police%20and%20Provincial%20Armed%20Constabulary%20(PAC)%20opened%20fire%20on%20the%20Muslims%20gathered%20there.%20The%20resultant%20deaths%20led%20to%20the%20spread%20of%20violence%20elsewhere%2C%20including%20the%20rural%20areas%20of%20Moradabad%2C%20Aligarh%2C%20Bareilly%20and%20beyond.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20recently%20as%20May%202023%2C%20the%20BJP-led%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20government%20of%20the%20state%20declared%20that%20they%20would%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fmoradabad-was-ups-first-big-riot-after-1947-8613856%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etable%20a%20report%20on%20the%20riots%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20UP%20assembly%2C%20over%20four%20decades%20since%20the%20violence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWriting%20about%20the%20riots%E2%80%99%20impact%20on%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20brass%20industry%2C%20economist%20Sami%20Uddin%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DSzQlpskiOKsC%26pg%3DPA254%26redir_esc%3Dy%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20communal%20violence%20which%20continued%20for%20about%20four%20months%20in%20Moradabad%20led%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Csudden%20fall%20in%20production%20and%20exports%20of%20the%20industry%E2%80%9D.%20Azam%20Ansari%20also%20said%20that%20the%20scale%20of%20violence%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccaused%20the%20most%20hardships%20for%20Muslim%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekarigars%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20piece-rate%20workers%E2%80%9D%20owing%20to%20the%20imposition%20of%20curfews%20and%20scarcity%20of%20raw%20materials.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20as%20the%20industry%20bounced%20back%20over%20the%20next%20three%20decades%2C%20several%20workers%20and%20industry%20insiders%20now%20express%20a%20sense%20of%20foreboding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERizwan*%2C%20a%20prominent%20Muslim%20exporter%20in%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20Asalatpur%20area%2C%20speaking%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20said%20that%20capital%20and%20access%20to%20upward%20mobility%20amongst%20Muslims%20in%20the%20industry%20has%20been%20waning.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20least%20three%20generations%20of%20my%20family%20have%20been%20in%20this%20business%20and%20we%20have%20seen%20its%20dividends%20till%20around%202010%2C%20but%20my%20children%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20join%20this%20line%20of%20work.%20They%20will%20settle%20abroad%20for%20good.%20There%20is%20very%20little%20scope%20to%20grow%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20admitted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20said%20that%20industries%20that%20once%20offered%20socio-economic%20mobility%20for%20local%20Muslims%2C%20were%20now%20being%20targeted%20across%20UP%2C%20albeit%20%E2%80%9Csilently%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20moves%20of%20the%20Yogi%20Adityanath-led%20BJP%20government%20in%20UP%20in%202017%20was%20enforcing%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Estricter%20guidelines%20on%20the%20sale%20of%20meat%2C%20as%20well%20as%20closure%20of%20several%20private%20slaughterhouses.%20Coupled%20with%20draconian%20anti-cow%20slaughter%20laws%2C%20these%20changes%20have%20directly%20impacted%20the%20meat%20and%20leather%20industries%20in%20the%20state.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Micro%2C%20Small%20and%20Medium%20Enterprises%20(MSME)%20space%2C%20we%20can%20feel%20social%20pressures%20affecting%20our%20businesses%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rizwan%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20further%20emphasised%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMoradabad%E2%80%99s%20brass%20industry%20was%20dominated%20by%20Muslims%2C%20Aligarh%E2%80%99s%20locks%20industry%20has%20been%20dominated%20by%20Muslims.%20In%20Saharanpur%2C%20the%20wooden%20goods%20industry%2C%20then%20you%20have%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20zari-zardozi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ework%20and%20even%20Banarasi%20silks%20also%20see%20a%20strong%20Muslim%20presence%2C%20the%20leather%20hub%20of%20Kanpur-Unnao%20has%20always%20seen%20upward%20mobility%20for%20Muslims.%20Now%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eqasais%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(butchers)%20and%20hoteliers%20are%20being%20threatened%20for%20selling%20meat%2C%20our%20businesses%20being%20boycotted.%20While%20it%20is%20not%20always%20overt%20targeting%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20do%20sense%20an%20insidious%2C%20invisible%20attack%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENo%20state%20support%2C%20loss%20of%20artisan%20cards%20and%20a%20quiet%20exodus%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20being%20a%20Padma%20Shree%20awardee%2C%2075-year-old%20Dilshad%20Hussain%20believes%20that%20the%20brass%20business%20has%20become%20unsustainable.%20Hussain%20and%20his%20six%20children%2C%20as%20well%20as%20his%20wife%2C%20all%20work%20out%20of%20the%20bylanes%20of%20Kaitwali%20Masjid%20locality%20and%20have%20even%20received%20commissions%20for%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%2C%20foreign%20dignitaries%20and%20bureaucratic%20officials.%20%E2%80%9C%5BBut%5D%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20regular%20job%2C%20I%20get%20commissioned%20for%20an%20order%20around%20once%20in%20three%20months%2C%20then%20there%20are%20months%20where%20no%20work%20is%20given%20at%20all%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20he%20and%20all%20his%20children%20have%20won%20state%20and%20national-level%20awards%20for%20the%20engraving%20work.%20He%20also%20undertakes%20training%20programs%2C%20seminars%20and%20workshops%20as%20part%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Skill%20India%E2%80%99%20initiative.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20where%20once%20upon%20a%20time%2C%20we%20could%20make%20100%20pieces%20in%20one%20go%2C%20we%20now%20receive%20only%20limited%20advance%20pay%20for%20orders%20and%20can%20make%20just%2050%20to%2060%20pieces%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20septuagenarian%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAkarigar%20in%20the%20industry%20earns%20approximately%20Rs%2012-13%2C000%20on%20average%2C%20and%20at%20best%20a%20monthly%20earning%20of%20Rs%2020%2C000.%20Adding%20to%20their%20woes%20is%20the%20central%20government%E2%80%99s%20halting%20of%20various%20schemes.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20policies%20introduced%20between%202004-08%2C%20all%20of%20them%20have%20effectively%20stopped.%20First%2C%20there%20was%20the%20artisans%20credit%20card%20yojana%20where%20loans%20were%20given%20to%20artisans%20at%20a%204%25%20yearly%20interest.%20Now%20that%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20case%20and%20we%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.artisan.gov.in%2FServiceDetails.aspx%3Fl_title%3DMudra%2520Loan%26level%3D3%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMUDRA%20loans%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%2012%25%20yearly%20interest%20with%20taxes%20that%20come%20to%20almost%2022%25%20annually.%20Artisans%E2%80%99%20identification%20cards%20have%20also%20stopped%20being%20circulated%2C%20last%20reissued%20in%202017%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ansari%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20484px)%2085vw%2C%20484px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26170929%2Funnamed-1-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22484%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26170929%2Funnamed-1-1.jpg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26170929%2Funnamed-1-1-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26170929%2Funnamed-1-1-768x1024.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665265%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22646%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAshaqeel%20and%20Mujeeb-ur-Rahman%20working%20next%20to%20a%20furnace%20to%20cast%20the%20metal%20into%20moulds%2C%20using%20silt.%20Photo%3A%20Sabah%20Gurmat%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20though%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Textiles%20under%20the%20development%20commissioner%20for%20handicrafts%20allows%20applications%20for%20obtaining%20Aadhaar-linked%20photo%20identity%20cards%2C%20Ansari%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccards%20are%20not%20being%20issued%20at%20the%20moment%E2%80%9D.%20In%202014%2C%20the%20textiles%20ministry%20had%20passed%20a%20decision%20to%20link%20the%20cards%20to%20each%20artisan%E2%80%99s%20Aadhaar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThe%20advantage%20of%20this%20was%20that%20if%20a%20karigar%20goes%20abroad%2C%20then%20his%20Aadhaar-linked%20card%20would%20show%20his%20identity%20as%20that%20of%20an%20artisan%20affiliated%20to%20the%20Indian%20government.%20This%20provided%20them%20much-needed%20identification%20to%20go%20showcase%20their%20work%20at%20international%20exhibits%20and%20fairs.%20It%20also%20gave%20them%20the%20patronage%20that%20they%20were%20official%2C%20government-recognised%20artisans%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ansari%20added.%20Rahman%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20smaller%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekarigars%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewere%20earlier%20able%20to%20go%20to%20nearby%20states%20and%20showcase%20their%20work%20in%20exhibits%20across%20cities%2C%20but%20that%20has%20taken%20a%20hit%20now.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Adityanath%20government%20has%20been%20making%20a%20big%20push%20for%20their%20%E2%80%98One%20District%20One%20Product%E2%80%99%20scheme%20to%20boost%20industrial%20production%20and%20exports%2C%20the%20institution%20developed%20for%20training%20and%20technological-development%20in%20the%20brass%20industry%2C%20lies%20stagnant.%C2%A0%20The%20Metal%20Handicrafts%20Service%20Center%20was%20inaugurated%20in%20the%20city%20in%201983%2C%20but%20it%20was%20relaunched%20just%20last%20year%20in%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20decades%2C%20it%20seems%20as%20if%20there%20was%20a%20vested%20interest%20in%20letting%20this%20institute%20stagnate%20and%20hence%20shut%20down%2C%20which%20would%20only%20affect%20the%20future%20generations%20and%20their%20economic%20prospects%20in%20the%20brass%20industry.%20It%E2%80%99s%20locals%20who%20put%20up%20a%20fight%20to%20ensure%20training%20and%20skill%20development%20takes%20place%20here.%20During%20the%20pandemic%20(2020-2021)%2C%20neither%20state%20nor%20central%20government%20gave%20grants%20to%20the%20institute%20and%20people%20had%20to%20earn%20their%20salaries%20by%20themselves%2C%20by%20holding%20paid%20courses%20here%20instead%20of%20the%20teaching%20staff%20being%20paid%20by%20the%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ravindra%20Kumar%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20centre.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKumar%20pointed%20out%20how%20many%20small%20exporters%20and%20metal-traders%20from%20across%20the%20country%20would%20come%20here%20for%20upskilling%2C%20testing%20of%20products%20and%20certification.%20%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20over%20800%20types%20of%20tests%20here%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20completely%20controlled%20by%20the%20government%20and%20is%20an%20accredited%20laboratory.%20But%20our%20salaries%20aren%E2%80%99t%20paid%20by%20the%20government%20so%20we%20have%20to%20charge%20fees%20for%20training%20or%20conducting%20workshops%20to%20pay%20our%20salaries%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENotably%2C%20he%20informed%20that%20other%20MSME%20enterprises%20receive%20both%20training%20and%20salaries%20from%20the%20ministry%20of%20textiles%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Handloom%20Technology%20and%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Carpet%20Technology.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20repeatedly%20been%20writing%20letters%20to%20the%20ministry%20seeking%20financial%20assistance%20of%20just%20Rs%204%20crores.%20If%20the%20other%20institutes%20are%20getting%20Rs%205%20crores%2C%20or%20Rs%20100%20crores%2C%20at%20least%20give%20us%204%20crore%20to%20make%20this%20space%20world-class%20and%20better-equipped%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kumar%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESeen%20as%20%E2%80%98polluters%E2%80%99%2C%20metal%20workers%20forced%20out%20of%20jobs%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20National%20Green%20Tribunal%20(NGT)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fe-waste-on-ramganga-banks-ngt-summons-up-chief-secretary-5349212%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereprimanded%20state%20authorities%20in%202018%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20disposal%20of%20electronic%20waste%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Ramganga%20river%20in%20Moradabad%2C%20the%20UP%20government%20decided%20to%20shut%20down%20metal%20factories%20operating%20in%20the%20region%20citing%20a%20violation%20of%20pollution%20norms.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20at%20least%2075%20brass-making%20units%20were%20closed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20workers%20such%20as%20Aashaqeel%20suffer%20losses.%20%E2%80%9CGovernment%20officials%20have%20flagged%20pollution%20as%20a%20problem%20for%20the%20last%208%20to%2010%20years.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20been%20asked%20to%20relocate%20or%20shift%20to%20different%20methods%20of%20production.%20The%20government%20is%20saying%20these%20are%20the%20NGT%E2%80%99s%20orders%20so%20we%20must%20comply.%20But%20at%20least%20tell%20us%20about%20alternatives%20then%2C%20or%20do%20we%20just%20stop%20making%20our%20living%20and%20let%20this%20industry%20die%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26171050%2Funnamed-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22606%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26171050%2Funnamed-2.jpg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26171050%2Funnamed-2-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26171050%2Funnamed-2-768x1024.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665267%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22808%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBrass-casting%20workers%20in%20localities%20like%20Islam%20Nagar%20and%20Peerzada%20spend%2010%20to%2012%20hours%20a%20day%20working%20in%20cramped%20kilns%20and%20operating%20the%20furnace%20without%20any%20protective%20gear.%20Photo%3A%20Sabah%20Gurmat%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%2053-year-old%20brass%20urn%20manufacturer%20Raees%20Ahmed%2C%20no%20one%20in%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20upcoming%20generations%20will%20enter%20this%20line%20of%20work.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20engraved%20urns%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eare%20exported%20to%20the%20USA%20and%20Europe%20and%20used%20to%20store%20the%20remains%20of%20loved%20ones%2C%20or%20items%20of%20the%20deceased%20such%20as%20spectacles%2C%20cufflinks%2C%20a%20watch%2C%20etc%20by%20Christians%20in%20foreign%20countries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAhmed%20claims%20that%20work%20has%20dropped%20down%20to%20just%2025%25%20of%20what%20it%20once%20was.%20Where%20once%2C%20an%20artisan%20made%20Rs%20500%20they%20now%20make%20Rs%20350%20at%20best.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20father%2C%20his%20father%20and%20his%20brothers%2C%20and%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20father%20were%20all%20associated%20with%20the%20brass%20industry%20in%20one%20way%20or%20another.%20People%20now%20realise%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20money%20in%20this%20line%20of%20work%2C%20and%20high%20cost%20of%20production.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20people%20making%20ingots%20and%20undertaking%20the%20casting%20of%20metals%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20face%20the%20brunt%20of%20pollution%20norms.%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%20I%20had%20around%2050%20artisans%20doing%20the%20engraving%20work%2C%20now%20that%20has%20gone%20down%20to%2015%20people.%20A%20lot%20of%20artisans%20have%20migrated%20out%20of%20Moradabad%2C%20and%20gone%20to%20Bangladesh%20and%20Nepal%20to%20work.%20Others%20have%20taken%20to%20jobs%20like%20driving%20e-rickshaws%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ahmed%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E52-year-old%20Haji%20Amin%20concurs.%20Amin%20has%20been%20working%20for%20the%20past%2024%20years%20manufacturing%20Buddhist%20singing%20bowls%20made%20up%20of%20brass%20and%20aluminium.%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20we%20had%20around%2030%20people%20working%20at%20our%20workshop%2C%20now%20it%E2%80%99s%20just%20five%20people.%20Our%20work%20particularly%20declined%20after%20GST%20was%20introduced.%20Where%20an%20item%20was%20earlier%20sold%20for%20Rs%20100%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20now%20retailing%20at%20Rs%20120.%20Because%20countries%20like%20Nepal%20have%20caught%20up%20and%20now%20compete%20with%20us%20on%20pricing%20for%20buyers%2C%20it%20is%20manufacturers%20in%20Moradabad%20who%E2%80%99ve%20suffered%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amin%20pointed%20out.%20Since%20raw%20materials%20which%20go%20into%20smelting%20the%20brass%20are%20taxed%20under%20GST%2C%20costs%20of%20production%20have%20now%20risen%20and%20so%20have%20the%20prices%20for%20finished%20products.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20producers%20from%20the%20city%20are%20losing%20out%20to%20cheaper%20products%20from%20Nepal%20and%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20said%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbig%20chunk%E2%80%9D%20of%20karigars%20had%20migrated%20to%20Nepal%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20the%20Gulf%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20rising%20unemployment%20here.%20Which%20youth%20wants%20to%20work%20amongst%20dust%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20safety%20next%20to%20a%20furnace%20and%20this%20heat%3F%20My%20father%20and%20grandfather%20were%20associated%20with%20this%20line%20of%20work.%20I%20have%20four%20sons%2C%20all%20of%20them%20are%20working%20in%20the%20same%20industry%20but%20my%20grandchildren%20will%20not.%20It%E2%80%99s%20getting%20harder%20for%20our%20community%20to%20feel%20safe%20as%20it%20is%2C%20so%20if%20a%20child%20is%20well-educated%2C%20why%20make%20brass%20utensils%20when%20they%20can%20leave%20and%20aspire%20towards%20a%20good%20government%20job%3F%E2%80%9D%20Amin%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESabah%20Gurmat%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20This%20story%20is%20part%20of%20an%20ongoing%20series%20on%20the%20socio-economic%20decline%20of%20industries%20and%20businesses%20led%20by%20Muslims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EReporting%20for%20her%20article%20was%20supported%20by%20the%20International%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Media%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20Howard%20G.%20Buffett%20Fund%20for%20Women%20Journalists.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690450228000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26171427%2Feb8b8040-6657-4a57-9818-4908f7c8ce72.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fin-indias-brass-city-an-overwhelmingly-muslim-workforce-stares-at-a-looming-crisis%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Industries%20that%20once%20offered%20socio-economic%20mobility%20for%20local%20Muslims%20are%20now%20being%20targeted%20across%20UP%2C%20albeit%20%E2%80%9Csilently%26quot%3B%2C%20some%20believe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fin-indias-brass-city-an-overwhelmingly-muslim-workforce-stares-at-a-looming-crisis%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2