%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20mineral%20monopoly%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnswers%20to%20these%20begin%20with%20an%20understanding%20of%20how%20supply%20chains%20for%20many%20of%20these%20minerals%20and%20their%20derivatives%20are%20currently%20controlled%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20power%20structures%20these%20supply%20chains%20represent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20pages%20of%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fus.macmillan.com%2Fbooks%2F9781250284297%2Fcobaltred%5C%22%3E%20the%20bestselling%20book%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fus.macmillan.com%2Fbooks%2F9781250284297%2Fcobaltred%5C%22%3ECobalt%20Red%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20author%20Siddharth%20Kara%20describes%20a%20modern%20geopolitical%20quandary.%20Half%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20reserves%20of%20cobalt%20lie%20in%20a%20400%20sqkm%20crescent%20running%20from%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo%20(DRC)%20to%20northern%20Zambia%2C%20writes%20Kara%20in%20his%20book%20about%20the%20unfettered%20mining%20of%20the%20mineral%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20mining%20here%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20depots%20that%20collect%20cobalt%20ore%20from%20miners%20to%20the%20units%20that%20process%20it%20%E2%80%93%20is%20dominated%20by%20the%20Chinese.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20of%20my%20last%20ground%20count%20in%20November%202021%2C%20there%20were%20nineteen%20major%20industrial%20copper-cobalt%20mining%20complexes%20operating%20in%20(Congo%E2%80%99s)%20Haut-Katanga%20and%20Lualala%20provinces%2C%20fifteen%20of%20which%20were%20owned%20or%20financed%20by%20Chinese%20mining%20companies%2C%E2%80%9D%20writes%20Kara.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20just%20the%20start.%20Semi-processed%20cobalt%20from%20these%20mines%20is%20exported%20to%20commercial-grade%20refiners%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20in%20China.%20%E2%80%9CIn%202021%2C%20China%20produced%2075%20percent%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20refined%20cobalt%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20writes.%20%E2%80%9CT