0UN%20Population%20Estimates.%3Cbr%3E%5CnLabour%20force%20participation%20rates%20based%20in%20ILO%E2%80%99s%20modelled%20estimates%20via%20The%20World%20Bank%3C%2Fcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20while%20India%E2%80%99s%20working%20age%20demographic%20group%20was%20almost%20comparable%20in%20size%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%2C%20its%20labour%20force%20was%20significantly%20smaller%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20its%20much%20lower%20rates%20of%20female%20labour%20force%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20when%20is%20India%20likely%20to%20overtake%20China%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20assume%20constant%20LFPR%20rates%20as%20the%20most%20recent%20ones%20for%20both%20countries%2C%20it%20will%20take%20another%2027%20years%20for%20that%20to%20happen.%20It%20is%20only%20in%202051%20when%20India%20will%20have%20more%20people%20in%20the%20labour%20force%20(15-64)%20than%20China%20(assuming%20everything%20else%20remains%20constant).%20These%20calculations%20are%20based%20on%20UN%20populations%20estimates%20available%20for%20all%20years%20up%20till%202100.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%204%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdn%2F16062023%2Flabour-force-estimation%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3ELooks%20like%20your%20browser%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20iframes.%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E(To%20view%20this%20visualisation%20fully%20on%20your%20device%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdn%2F16062023%2Flabour-force-estimation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20India%E2%80%99s%20LFPR%20were%20to%20increase%20to%2060%20percent%2C%20this%20could%20happen%20by%202040.%20(Users%20can%20enter%20different%20LFPR%20values%20in%20Figure%204%20to%20see%20how%20this%20timeline%20changes%20in%20different%20scenarios).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20to%20exceed%20China%E2%80%99s%20in%20absolute%20numbers%20by%202030%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20LFPR%20would%20need%20to%20increase%20sharply%20from%20the%20current%20level%20of%20roughly%2058%20percent%20(the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20by%20usual%20status%20for%20the%2015-64%20age%20group%20as%20estimated%20by%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%2C%202021-22)%20to%2071%20percent%20for%20the%20next%20seven%20years.%20There%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20such%20drastic%20improvement%20could%20be%20achieved%20in%20a%20short%20span%20of%20time.%20Any%20increase%20in%20overall%20LFPR%20is%20contingent%20upon%20on%20improving%20the%20share%20of%20women%20in%20the%20labour%20force%2C%20which%20is%20not%20impossible%2C%20but%20would%20need%20a%20dedicated%20set%20of%20comprehensive%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20demographic%20and%20gender%20dividends%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mere%20existence%20of%20a%20larger%20working%20age%20population%20does%20not%20constitute%20a%20demographic%20dividend.%20For%20it%20to%20be%20a%20dividend%2C%20first%2C%20the%20working%20age%20population%20must%20be%20in%20the%20labour%20force.%20Second%2C%20they%20must%20be%20productively%20employed.%20Otherwise%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20in%20the%20working%20age%20group%20who%20are%20not%20productively%20employed%20can%20represent%20a%20huge%20challenge%20as%20the%20unfulfilled%20need%20for%20livelihood%20opportunities%20is%20a%20sure-fire%20recipe%20for%20discontent%20and%20unrest%20which%20can%20enhance%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20already%20grappling%20with%20a%20jobs%20crisis%2C%20as%20roughly%205.5%20million%20new%20jobs%20that%20the%20country%20needs%20are%20not%20getting%20created%2C%20which%20makes%20agriculture%20the%20sector%20of%20last%20resort%20for%20people%20to%20eke%20out%20a%20livelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20India%20is%20already%20grappling%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdecoding-womens-labour-force-participation-in-2021-22-what-the-periodic-labour-force-survey-shows%2F%5C%22%3Elow%20female%20LFPRs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20reason%20responsible%20for%20the%20low%20levels%20is%20undercounting%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20economic%20work%20on%20family%20enterprises.%20Accounting%20for%20this%20work%20raises%20LFPR%20estimates%2C%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20official%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Feconomicsurvey%2Fdoc%2Feschapter%2Fechap06.pdf%5C%22%3EEconomic%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20attempted%20to%20do.%20While%20recognizing%20women%E2%80%99s%20(unpaid)%20contribution%20to%20family%20enterprises%20is%20very%20important%2C%20it%20is%20not%20a%20substitute%20for%20paid%20work%2C%20the%20opportunities%20for%20which%20are%20not%20growing%20as%20rapidly%20as%20needed.%20There%20is%20dire%20need%20for%20expansion%20of%20rural%20non-farm%20employment%2C%20both%20for%20men%20and%20women%2C%20but%20especially%20crucial%20for%20women%20as%20they%20are%20unable%20to%20travel%20long%20distances%20to%20access%20work%2C%20due%20to%20their%20predominant%20responsibility%20for%20domestic%20chores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20rapid%20growth%20was%20in%20no%20small%20measure%20due%20to%20one%20element%20of%20their%20economic%20reforms%3A%20the%20expansion%20of%20rural%20industry%20via%20the%20Township%20and%20Village%20Enterprises%20(TVEs)%20that%20absorbed%20its%20massive%20workforce%20in%20small%2C%20labour%20intensive%2C%20nonfarm%20work%20opportunities.%20Between%201978%20(the%20start%20of%20the%20economic%20reforms)%20and%201995%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20rural%20industries%20grew%20over%2020%20percent%20per%20year%2C%20raising%20their%20share%20in%20industrial%20production%20from%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.elibrary.imf.org%2Fdisplay%2Fbook%2F9781557755421%2Fch013.xml%5C%22%3E3%20percent%20in%201971%20to%2030%20percent%20in%201990%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20bus%20that%20India%20seems%20to%20be%20missing.%20If%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20enough%20remunerative%20work%20for%20young%20people%20and%20women%2C%20a%20very%20large%20potential%20pool%20of%20talent%20will%20remain%20un-%20or%20underutilized%20and%20the%20much-vaunted%20demographic%20dividend%20will%20remain%20illusory%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESkill%20differences%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20big%20contrast%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20is%20seen%20in%20the%20training%2Fskill%20differences%20of%20the%20population.%20While%20in%20both%20countries%2C%20gross%20enrolment%20ratio%20for%20tertiary%20education%20(GETR)%20has%20been%20increasing%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20GETR%20in%202021%20was%20roughly%20half%20that%20of%20China%20in%202021%20(Figure%205).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%205%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F16062023%2Ffigure5.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3ELooks%20like%20your%20browser%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20iframes.%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20does%20China%20have%20a%20higher%20GETR%20compared%20to%20India%20for%20both%20men%20and%20women%2C%20but%20the%20relative%20difference%20has%20also%20increased%20over%20recent%20years.%20In%202015%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20GETR%20was%201.7%20times%20that%20of%20India.%20By%202021%2C%20it%20was%20twice%20the%20level%20of%20India.%20The%20female%20gap%20remained%20roughly%20constant%20over%20the%20period%20(from%201.9%20to%202.1)%2C%20whereas%20the%20male%20gap%20increased%20from%201.6%20to%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20Elephant-Dragon%20Tango%20will%20continue%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20sober%20reflection%20reveals%20that%20while%20India%20will%20become%20the%20most%20populous%20country%2C%20it%20is%20not%20about%20to%20overtake%20China%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20bigger%20and%20more%20educated%20labour%20force.%20This%20is%20not%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20continued%20growth%20of%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20is%20free%20of%20its%20own%20set%20of%20challenges.%20In%20addition%20to%20battling%20geo-political%20challenges%20to%20its%20global%20expansion%20plans%2C%20China%20has%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20shrinking%20labour%20force%2C%20ageing%20population%20and%20boosting%20productivity%20growth.%20How%20acutely%20these%20challenges%20affect%20the%20Chinese%20rate%20of%20growth%20is%20a)%20a%20subject%20matter%20for%20another%20article%20and%20b)%20something%20only%20time%20will%20tell.%20This%20piece%20focuses%20on%20the%20Elephant-Dragon%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncreasing%20female%20LFPRs%2C%20not%20only%20via%20correctly%20measuring%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20but%20via%20creation%20of%20an%20ecosystem%20that%20provides%20remunerative%20and%20sustainable%20livelihoods%20close%20to%20home%20(read%20rural%20nonfarm%20employment)%20and%20investing%20in%20an%20educated%2C%20skilled%20and%20healthy%20workforce%20should%20be%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20priority%2C%20based%20on%20its%20own%20demographic%20reality%2C%20not%20just%20because%20of%20a%20presumed%20competition%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAshwini%20Deshpande%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%2C%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20and%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20ashwini.deshpande%40ashoka.edu.in.%20Akshi%20Chawla%20is%20editor%2C%20CEDA%2C%20and%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20akshi.chawla%40ashoka.edu.in.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fthe-elephant-is-set-to-overtake-the-dragon-or-is-it%2F%5C%22%3ECEDA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690447209000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27133636%2F6283735999_47c3124b38_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findia-china-population-labour-force%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22...if%20we%20assume%20the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20for%20both%20countries%20will%20remain%20constant%2C%20and%20so%20will%20other%20factors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findia-china-population-labour-force%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kuwait%20hangs%20five%2C%20including%202015%20mosque%20bombing%20convict%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690446381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102166459%2Cimgsize-293304.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkuwait-hangs-five-including-2015-mosque-bombing-convict%2Farticleshow%2F102166526.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102166526